Definition: an odd or fanciful or capricious idea
Example: the theatrical notion of disguise is associated with disaster in his stories; he had a whimsy about flying to the moon; whimsy can be humorous to someone with time to enjoy it
Synonyms: whim, whimsy, adj, all, arbitrary, whimsical, whimsey, idea, an, odd, or, fanciful, capricious, the, theatrical, of, disguise, is, associated, with, disaster, in, his, stories, he, had, a, about, flying, to, moon, can, be, humorous, someone, time, enjoy, it
Category: noun.cognition
